RPC_GSS_MAX_DATA_LENG... BSD Library Functions Manual RPC_GSS_MAX_DATA_LENG...

NAME
     rpc_gss_max_data_length â€” calculate maximum data size

SYNOPSIS
     #include <rpc/rpcsec_gss.h>

     int
     rpc_gss_max_data_length(AUTH *auth, int max_tp_unit_len);

DESCRIPTION
     Calculate the maximum message size that will fit into a packet of size
     max_tp_unit_len, given the current service and QoP setting.

PARAMETERS
     auth             A handle to a RPCSEC_GSS security context

     max_tp_unit_len  Maximum packet size of the underlying transport protocol

RETURN VALUES
     The maximum message size that can be encoded

AVAILABILITY
     The rpc_gss_max_data_length() function is part of libtirpc.

SEE ALSO
     rpc(3), gssapi(3), rpcsec_gss(3)

AUTHORS
     This manual page was written by Doug Rabson <dfr@FreeBSD.org>.

